    %% NOTES
    %% ============================================================================
    %%
    %% TECHNICAL DETAILS:
    %%
    %% 1. How sharing works under the hood:
    %%    - Provider and consumer share same underlying storage (S3/Azure/GCS)
    %%    - Share object contains metadata pointers to micro-partitions
    %%    - Consumer queries read directly from provider's storage
    %%    - No data duplication (zero-copy architecture)
    %%
    %% 2. Security model:
    %%    - Consumer CANNOT see provider's data outside the share
    %%    - Consumer CANNOT modify shared data (read-only)
    %%    - Provider controls exact objects shared (tables/views)
    %%    - Secure views enforce row/column-level security
    %%
    %% 3. Performance:
    %%    - Shared data queries same speed as local tables
    %%    - Consumer's warehouse performs all compute
    %%    - Partition pruning works transparently
    %%    - Result cache per consumer (isolated)
    %%
    %% 4. Limitations:
    %%    - Provider and consumer must be on same cloud provider (or use replication)
    %%    - Consumer can only SELECT (no INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE)
    %%    - Consumer cannot create views on shared data (immutable)
    %%    - Time Travel on shared data uses provider's retention settings
    %%
    %% 5. Cross-region/cross-cloud:
    %%    - Direct sharing: Same cloud provider, any region (some caveats)
    %%    - With replication: Any cloud provider, any region
    %%    - Replication cost: $0.002/GB + storage in target region
    %%
    %% COST EXAMPLES:
    %%
    %% Example 1: Small dataset (10 GB), 1 consumer, low usage
    %% - Provider storage: 10 GB × $30/TB = $0.30/month
    %% - Consumer compute: 1 hour/month × 2 credits = $6/month
    %% - Total: $6.30/month
    %%
    %% Example 2: Large dataset (1 TB), 10 consumers, heavy usage
    %% - Provider storage: 1 TB × $30 = $30/month (paid once, not per consumer!)
    %% - Consumer compute (avg per consumer): 20 hours/month × 4 credits = 80 credits = $240/month
    %% - Total: $30 (provider) + $2,400 (all consumers) = $2,430/month
    %% - vs. copying data: 10 TB total storage = $300/month + compute = much more expensive
    %%
    %% ============================================================================
